items.title: Vertx Awesome
items.content_text: ### Web Frameworks * [Vert.x Web (‚≠ê1.1k)](https://github.com/vert-x3/vertx-web) - Full featured web toolkit for Vert.x. ### Authentication Authorisation * [Vert.x Auth Mongo (‚≠ê15)](https://github.com/vert-x3/vertx-auth/tree/master/vertx-auth-mongo) - Vert.x support for Kotlin coroutines. ### Vert.x Event Bus Clients * [JavaScript](https://www.npmjs.com/package/vertx3-eventbus-client) - JavaScript event bus client. * [Rust (‚≠ê10)](https://github.com/aesteve/vertx-eventbus-client-rs) - Event bus client for Rust applications through TCP. ### Cluster Managers * [Hazelcast Cluster Manager (‚≠ê78)](https://github.com/vert-x3/vertx-hazelcast) - Hazelcast cluster manager. * [Ignite Cluster Manager (‚≠ê34)](https://github.com/vert-x3/vertx-ignite) - Ignite cluster manager. * [Zookeeper Cluster Manager (‚≠ê73)](https://github.com/vert-x3/vertx-zookeeper) - Zookeeper cluster manager. * [Infinispan Cluster Manager (‚≠ê15)](https://github.com/vert-x3/vertx-infinispan) - Infinispan cluster manager. ### Cloud Support * [OpenShift DIY cartridge (‚≠ê1)](https://github.com/vert-x3/vertx-openshift-diy-quickstart) - OpenShift DIY Cartridge using Vert.x. * [OpenShift Vert.x cartridge (‚≠ê20)](https://github.com/vert-x3/vertx-openshift-cartridge) - OpenShift Vert.x Cartridge using Vert.x. ### Microservices * [Service Discovery (‚≠ê117)](https://github.com/vert-x3/vertx-service-discovery) - Vert.x Service Discovery. * [Circuit Breaker (‚≠ê64)](https://github.com/vert-x3/vertx-circuit-breaker) - Vert.x Circuit Breaker. * [Service Discovery - Consul (‚≠ê117)](https://github.com/vert-x3/vertx-service-discovery) - [Consul](https://www.consul.io/) extension to Vert.x Service Discovery. * [Service Discovery - Docker links (‚≠ê117)](https://github.com/vert-x3/vertx-service-discovery) - [Docker](https://www.docker.com/) extension to Vert.x Service Discovery. * [Service Discovery - Kubernetes (‚≠ê117)](https://github.com/vert-x3/vertx-service-discovery) - [Kubernetes](http://kubernetes.io/) extension to Vert.x Service Discovery. * [Service Discovery - Redis backend (‚≠ê117)](https://github.com/vert-x3/vertx-service-discovery) - [Redis](http://redis.io/) storage backend for Vert.x Service Discovery. ### Service Factory * [Service Factory (‚≠ê21)](https://github.com/vert-x3/vertx-service-factory) - Vert.x Service Factory. * [Maven Service Factory (‚≠ê13)](https://github.com/vert-x3/vertx-maven-service-factory) - Maven Vert.x Service Factory. * [HTTP Service Factory (‚≠ê9)](https://github.com/vert-x3/vertx-http-service-factory) - Vert.x HTTP Service Factory. ### Testing * [Vert.x Unit (‚≠ê32)](https://github.com/vert-x3/vertx-unit) - Async polyglot unit testing for Vert.x. * [Vert.x JUnit5 (‚≠ê44)](https://github.com/vert-x3/vertx-junit5) - Async unit testing for Vert.x with junit5. * [Vert.x WireMongo (‚≠ê10)](https://github.com/noenv/vertx-wiremongo) - Lightweight MongoDB mocking for Vert.x ### Development Tools * [Vert.x shell (‚≠ê38)](https://github.com/vert-x3/vertx-shell) - Allows for interaction with Vert.x from the command line. ### Distribution * [Vert.x Stack (‚≠ê121)](https://github.com/vert-x3/vertx-stack) - Vert.x + the endorsed modules. ### Examples * [Vert.x blueprint - Microservice application (‚≠ê781)](https://github.com/sczyh30/vertx-blueprint-microservice) - The official Vert.x blueprint showing how to build a complex microservice application. * [Vert.x blueprint - Job Queue (‚≠ê139)](https://github.com/sczyh30/vertx-blueprint-job-queue) - The official Vert.x blueprint showing how to build a distributed job processing application. * [Vert.x blueprint - TODO backend (‚≠ê181)](https://github.com/sczyh30/vertx-blueprint-todo-backend) - items.title: Awesome Ai in Finance
items.content_text:
### Papers

*   [The Theory of Speculation L. Bachelier, 1900](http://www.radio.goldseek.com/bachelier-thesis-theory-of-speculation-en.pdf) - The influences which determine the movements of the Stock Exchange are.
*   [Brownian Motion in the Stock Market Osborne, 1959](http://m.e-m-h.org/Osbo59.pdf) - The common-stock prices can be regarded as an ensemble of decisions in statistical equilibrium.
*   [Dragon-Kings, Black Swans and the Prediction of Crises Didier Sornette](https://arxiv.org/pdf/0907.4290.pdf) - The power laws in the distributions of event sizes under a broad range of conditions in a large variety of systems.
*   [Financial Trading as a Game: A Deep Reinforcement Learning Approach](https://arxiv.org/pdf/1807.02787.pdf) - Deep reinforcement learning provides a framework toward end-to-end training of such trading agent.
*   [Machine Learning for Trading](https://cims.nyu.edu/~ritter/ritter2017machine.pdf) - With an appropriate choice of the reward function, reinforcement learning techniques can successfully handle the risk-averse case.

### Courses & Books & Blogs

*   [Advances in Financial Machine Learning](https://www.amazon.com/Advances-Financial-Machine-Learning-Marcos-ebook/dp/B079KLDW21/ref=sr_1_1?s=books\&ie=UTF8\&qid=1541717436\&sr=1-1) - Using advanced ML solutions to overcome real-world investment problems.

### Time Series Data

*   üåü [Personae (‚≠ê1.4k)](https://github.com/Ceruleanacg/Personae) - Implements and environment of Deep Reinforcement Learning & Supervised Learning for Quantitative Trading.
